uvenated star formation due to\naccreted gas in older disks provided that the gas does not disrupt the\nstructure of the galaxy and the resulting star formation is not too recent and\nbursty. ESF-ETGs may typify an important subpopulation of galaxies that can\nlinger in the green valley for up to several Gyrs, based on their resemblance\nto nearby gas-rich green valley galaxies with low-level ongoing star formation.\n(abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Oct 2012 20:42:32 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 24 Oct 2012 15:56:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2012-11-22"}
